{
  "_how_to": [
    "Add a new app:",
    "  'keyword': {",
    "    'cmd':     'start command',        -- terminal command used to launch the app, e.g. 'firefox'",
    "    'name':    'Display name',         -- shown in confirmations and responses",
    "    'class':   'window class',         -- KWin window class, check with xprop WM_CLASS",
    "    'title':   'window title',         -- part of the window title, check with xprop WM_NAME",
    "    'flatpak': 'com.example.App'       -- optional, only for Flatpak apps",
    "  }",
    "",
    "Multiple keywords for the same app are allowed, e.g. 'vscode' and 'vs code'.",
    "For private or machine-specific paths, create config/apps.local.json.",
    "Example for an AppImage: {'myapp': {'cmd': '/home/you/Applications/MyApp.AppImage', 'name': 'My App', 'class': 'myapp', 'title': 'My App'}}",
    "apps.local.json is ignored by Git and overrides or extends this file.",
    "Find a Flatpak ID with: flatpak list --columns=name,application",
    "Find a window class with: xprop WM_CLASS, then click the window"
